name: Turuki Health Care - Mangere
services-description:
This is a walk in clinic as well as we take bookings.

To make a booking please call 09 275 5788 or 0800 4935523464 (0800 4wellbeing)

We are currently vaccinating groups 1, 2 and 3 which includes Māori and Pacific over 55 years of age.

Other people over 16 years of age can call in to go on a back up list for when we have vaccinations left over (which is most days).

Booking are made from Monday - Friday 9am - 4.30 and Saturday - Sunday 9am -1pm.

Getting a COVID-19 vaccine is an important step you can take to protect yourself, your kaumātua and whānau from the effects of the virus. For more information on the COVID-19 vaccines and eligibility visit immunisation.northernregion.health.nz.

If you are getting a flu, MMR or other vaccine, it will affect timing of the COVID-19 vaccination. Please discuss with your health provider.

services-description:
COVID-19 vaccinations available by appointment only. This is not a walk in clinic.

You can book a vaccine if YOU or a Whānau member in your household are;

  • Māori or Pacific from age 16+
  • Kaumatua, People 65+
  • Have a chronic disease (diabetes, cardiac, respiratory, asthma etc.)
  • Have a mental health condition 
  • Are an essential frontline worker.

Please call our friendly staff to book your appointment on 09 263 7770

Appointment available Mon - Fri 8am - 4.30pm & Sat , Sun 2pm - 8pm

The more of us that get vaccinated the safer our country will be, and we stand a greater chance of the borders opening and for us Kiwis to return to a more normal existence. 

Every New Zealander over the age of 16 will be entitled to two Comirnaty Pfizer/BioNTech vaccines, given at least 3 weeks apart. From the experience of our own staff the vaccinations are very well tolerated, and we highly recommend them. We will provide more vaccine information in due course but included are some links to some trusted sites.

Please phone to make an appointment for Reporoa on 07 333 7301 or Kaingaroa on 07 366 9718 for assistance or advice as we operate in the community after this time until 4 pm when Health Reporoa closes. Staff maybe busy doing District Nursing, Public Health in Schools or Health Checks out and about in the community and may not be avalaible until the next day when clinic opens again.

In an Emergency ring 111 and speak to the operator. 

We are closed for all Public Holidays. District Nursing Services as prearranged at this time.

name: Cromwell Family Practice
services-description:
Please do not ring the practice for a booking, WAIT to receive a booking invitation from your GP or other health provider. We are concentrating on our own patients, please wait and book with your own local GP or clinic.

This is not a walk in clinic.  You MUST have a booked appointment. This is a region wide booking system, we do not have extra vaccine to supply to walk ins.

Appointments are currently Thursday afternoons.

If you receive an invite, and cannot access the booking system for any reason, email us info@cromwellfamilypractice.co.nz, or call 0800 829 768 for help.

At this stage we are vaccinating (including second dose if first dose given elsewhere)

  • Healthcare workers not already done
  • Border workers not already done
  • Everyone over 65
  • Anyone with chronic health conditions eg diabetes, heart problems, asthma or COPD, cancer patients, stroke etc
  • Anyone else considered high risk
  • You must wait 2 weeks after your flu shot

additional-contact-details: To Book an Appointment below, you will need to be set up on our patient portal. If you are not yet registered please contact our reception team on 09 827 8888 or welcome@healthnewlynn.co.nz to find out how.
location: Totara Health, 1 McCrae Way, New Lynn, Auckland

name: HealthCentral
services-description:
The Southern District is rolling out the vaccine to Group 3 in the Ministry of Health sequencing framework in a staged model. Currently, eligible groups are:

  • People aged 65+
  • People with relevant underlying health conditions
  • Disabled people
  • Pregnant people

Please wait to receive a booking invitation from your GP or other health provider.

Please note: Practices do not make the COVID bookings – these are made via a nationwide booking system.

Getting a COVID-19 vaccine is an important step you can take to protect yourself, your kaumātua and whānau from the effects of the virus. For more information on the COVID-19 vaccines and eligibility visit Ministry of Health - COVID-19 vaccines.

If you are getting a flu, MMR or other vaccine, it will affect timing of the COVID-19 vaccination. Please discuss with your health provider.
service-subtypes: Anyone currently eligible can access
hours-description: After Hours: Please phone your normal GP practice and follow instructions. You will be transferred to a phone triaging service who will give you information on how to access our service after hours.

name: Northland COVID-19 Vaccination Centres
services-description:
For all information on COVID-19 Vaccination in Northland please visit the Northland DHB website

If you are on the list below, you can book for your COVID-19 vaccination.

  • Kuia, kaumātua and their whānau (the people they live with and their carers)
  • Frontline and other healthcare workers
  • Residents in Aged Residential Care Facilities - you don't need to book, we will be coming to your facility soon
  • People aged 50 years and over.

To register for your FREE COVID-19 Vaccine Phone - 0800 237 829 – 8am until 8pm - Monday to Sunday.  

  • The Northland COVID-19 0800 number (0800 237 829) is now staffed by a health call centre.  They are still experiencing a large volume of calls so please be patient.  
  • At this time we do not have any walk-in availability.  We will advise if this changes.  
  • You do not need to know your National Health Index number (NHI) to book an appointment.  
  • It is really important that you provide your full legal name – not an alias name or a nickname. 
  • Please do not turn up any earlier than 15 minutes prior to your appointment and we ask that you respect our COVID-19 Vaccination Community Clinic staff, who are working tirelessly to vaccinate our community.

Māori Health Providers are hosting COVID-19 vaccination clinics for Māori aged 16 years and older. For more information about making a booking or local walk-in clinics contact a provider on the number below.

Māori Health Provider Contact numbers 
 
Whakawhiti Ora Pai - 09 409 7880
  
Te Ha Oranga - 09-439 3013 Option 1
 
Ngāti Hine Health Trust - 0800 272 4842
 
Hokianga Health Trust - 09 4057509 ext. 709
 
Te Hau Ora O Ngāpuhi - 0800 484 006 Option 1
 
Te Hau Āwhiowhio ō Otangarei Trust - 0800 120 916
 
Te Hiku Hauroa - 0800 808 4024
 
Kāeo COVID-19 Vaccination Centre - 0800 465 236

name: Nelson and Tasman COVID-19 Vaccination Centres
services-description:
We are currently inviting people from Groups 1, 2 and 3 to get their vaccination; If you are in these groups you will be contacted directly by a booking team member using contact details held by your GP or healthcare provider. If you don’t have a GP you can register your contact details with Healthline on 0800 282 926. Once your contact details are up to date you do not need to do anything. We'll let you know when it's your turn. 

For more information on the roll out in Nelson, Tasman and Marlborough vist our website.

Getting a COVID-19 vaccine is an important step you can take to protect yourself, your kaumātua and whānau from the effects of the virus. For more information on the COVID-19 vaccines and eligibility visit Ministry of Health - COVID-19 vaccines

If you are getting a flu, MMR or other vaccine, it will affect timing of the COVID-19 vaccination. Please discuss with your health provider.
